Origin (DCO) — see CONTRIBUTING.md. Contributors retain copyright in
their own contributions; the project does not require copyright
assignment. The authoritative record of "who wrote what" is the git
log.

The maintainer (Keith Sinclair) holds copyright in:

  - Code authored by the maintainer directly.
  - Code committed by automated agents configured and operated by the
    maintainer (e.g. backend-developer, frontend-developer,
    test-developer, qa, requirements-analyst, planning-analyst —
    see lifecycle/config.yaml). These agents act as work-for-hire
    contributors under the maintainer's direction.

Other contributors hold copyright in their own contributions, signed
off via DCO.

